com.iota.iri.utils.thread

Interface SilentScheduledExecutorService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Executor, java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService, java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoundedScheduledExecutorService, DedicatedScheduledExecutorService

    public interface SilentScheduledExecutorService
extends java.util.concurrent.ScheduledExecutorService
    This interface extends the ScheduledExecutorService by providing additional methods to enqueue tasks without throwing a RejectedExecutionException exception.

    This can be useful when preventing additional tasks to run is no error but an intended design decision in the implementing class. In these cases raising an exception and catching it would cause too much unnecessary overhead (using Exceptions for control flow is an anti pattern).
